Much less a close relative.

01:24:30.960 --> 01:24:32.951
Well, I owe it all to you, Dad.

01:24:33.040 --> 01:24:36.874
You gave me all the advantages
that you never had.

01:24:38.000 --> 01:24:41.310
When Dad was my age,
he was a steampipe fitter.

01:24:43.480 --> 01:24:46.278
- Show her the calluses.
- Cut it out, Charlie.

01:24:47.840 --> 01:24:50.434
Who would like more
sour cream on their potato?

01:24:50.520 --> 01:24:52.476
Oh, I do, please.

01:24:56.320 --> 01:24:59.596
- I'm so sorry.
- It's all right, Teresa.

01:24:59.680 --> 01:25:02.797
These Portuguese girls
are very hard to train.

01:25:02.880 --> 01:25:05.838
I had one once who barely spoke...

01:25:06.400 --> 01:25:10.313
- English?
- I didn't mean your friend.

01:25:10.400 --> 01:25:12.630
- So what did you mean?
- Charles.

01:25:12.720 --> 01:25:14.790
I'm just clearin' the air, Dad.

01:25:14.880 --> 01:25:16.518
Aunt Tweedy...

01:25:16.600 --> 01:25:19.956
You can't even train
your own husband to sleep at home.

01:25:21.960 --> 01:25:25.316
And Dad's big frustration in life
is that he can't train me.

01:25:25.400 --> 01:25:27.391
- lsn't that right, Dad?
- Charlie!

01:25:27.480 --> 01:25:31.029
- Everyone knows I can't cut the mustard.
- You listen to me...

01:25:31.120 --> 01:25:33.315
If you can't train a golden boy like me,

01:25:33.400 --> 01:25:36.437
there's no way you're gonna train
a dumb Portuguese.

01:25:36.520 --> 01:25:39.910
- I said that's enough!
- OK. So I guess dinner is over.

01:25:43.600 --> 01:25:46.114
- Dammit, Charlie.
- Daisy?

01:25:46.320 --> 01:25:49.357
Charles? Charles, you come back here!

01:25:52.520 --> 01:25:56.035
Dais? Look, I'm sorry, all right?
But they deserved it.

01:25:56.120 --> 01:26:00.238
- I couldn't let 'em do that to you.
- Me? You did that for yourself.

01:26:00.320 --> 01:26:02.914
They were bein' real jerks!

01:26:03.000 --> 01:26:07.596
The only jerk at that table was you.
They were just being themselves.

01:26:07.680 --> 01:26:12.470
Bring home your poor Portuguese girlfriend
for dinner, shake up the family a little.

01:26:12.560 --> 01:26:16.189
- That's not true.
- I'm poor, and I hate it. I admit it.

01:26:17.720 --> 01:26:22.271
I even thought I was desperate,
but I'm not half as desperate as you are.

01:26:22.360 --> 01:26:25.352
I would never use you
to get at somebody.

01:26:26.440 --> 01:26:31.639
Your father didn't cheat his way out of
law school. You did that all on your own.

01:26:31.720 --> 01:26:33.711
Deal with it, Junior.

01:26:34.840 --> 01:26:37.274
You're not even good enough for me.

01:26:37.840 --> 01:26:40.479
Teresa? Can you give me a ride?

01:26:42.520 --> 01:26:44.954
I wanna go home.

01:26:53.600 --> 01:26:55.591
Kat...

01:27:03.120 --> 01:27:05.111
Oh, my God.

01:27:13.320 --> 01:27:14.355
Hi.

01:27:17.520 --> 01:27:19.397
Hi, Phoebe.

01:27:19.680 --> 01:27:22.194
Phoebe wanted to say goodbye.

01:27:28.040 --> 01:27:31.316
- Goodbye, Phoebe.
- Bye.

01:27:31.400 --> 01:27:33.630
- Keep going to the library, OK?
- OK.

01:27:38.160 --> 01:27:40.151
Take care.

01:27:46.280 --> 01:27:48.271
This is for you.

01:27:49.360 --> 01:27:51.351
It's for Yale.

01:27:52.880 --> 01:27:56.395
All those stars and comets
don't come cheap.

01:27:58.480 --> 01:28:00.471
Thank you.

01:28:00.560 --> 01:28:02.949
Goodbye, Tim.

01:28:04.440 --> 01:28:08.592
Yeah. Well, I guess... we better go.

01:28:09.680 --> 01:28:11.989
Bye, Kat.

01:28:37.840 --> 01:28:39.831
Kat?

01:28:48.000 --> 01:28:50.275
Are you out of your mind?

01:28:50.360 --> 01:28:52.794
If you initial this, you can still cash it.

01:28:52.880 --> 01:28:54.791
She doesn't need the money that bad.

01:28:54.880 --> 01:28:57.553
Oh, yeah? How is she gonna pay for Yale?

01:28:58.240 --> 01:29:00.231
She'll find a way.

01:29:27.240 --> 01:29:28.673
What now?

01:29:28.760 --> 01:29:31.399
..a hole in the wall
called the Mystic Pizza.

01:29:31.480 --> 01:29:34.278
- Moron.
- The atmosphere was rustic,

01:29:34.360 --> 01:29:36.635
the service was oversolicitous.

01:29:36.720 --> 01:29:40.872
- Is that good?
- Now, I am not a pizza person.

01:29:40.960 --> 01:29:44.236
I am not particularly
fond of cheesy cuisine,

01:29:44.320 --> 01:29:46.231
and this pizza is...

01:29:46.320 --> 01:29:49.153
How shall I say this? In a word...

01:29:49.320 --> 01:29:51.072
superb.

01:29:52.720 --> 01:29:56.395
I ordered the house speciality,
the Mystic Pizza. Mystic indeed.

01:29:56.640 --> 01:30:00.758
Exactly the right blend
of cheese and tomatoes and spices

01:30:00.840 --> 01:30:02.956
that I can't quite identify.

01:30:03.320 --> 01:30:06.153
You bet your ass you can't.

01:30:06.240 --> 01:30:09.710
That's the Mystic Pizza,
in Mystic, Connecticut.

01:30:09.800 --> 01:30:12.360
I have to give them my highest rating.

01:30:12.440 --> 01:30:14.715
Four stars.

01:30:17.880 --> 01:30:20.030
And you thought the man was a moron.

01:30:23.160 --> 01:30:25.196
Hello, Mystic Pizza.

01:30:25.920 --> 01:30:27.911
I beg your pardon?

01:30:29.400 --> 01:30:32.119
No, no. No reservations are necessary.

01:30:32.560 --> 01:30:34.596
Reservations!

01:30:34.680 --> 01:30:36.671
Yes. Yes, Main Street.

01:30:36.760 --> 01:30:39.035
This is Hector Pleshette wishing you...

01:30:46.440 --> 01:30:48.829
Bill, this is important.

01:30:48.920 --> 01:30:53.994
I don't want you to get the wrong idea,
but I gotta maintain my own identity.

01:30:54.080 --> 01:30:56.514
Maintain your own identity.

01:30:56.600 --> 01:30:59.478
Right. I mean,
I understand about commitment,

01:30:59.560 --> 01:31:01.710
and I love you more than anything.

01:31:01.800 --> 01:31:04.360
But you gotta know exactly where I stand,

01:31:04.440 --> 01:31:07.193
because absolutely nothing has changed.

01:31:08.440 --> 01:31:10.431
Except your name.

01:31:15.240 --> 01:31:17.231
Except my name.

01:32:14.600 --> 01:32:16.909
Who you wanna dance with, me or Kat?

01:32:17.000 --> 01:32:18.991
Not you.

01:32:30.080 --> 01:32:31.752
It's for Yale.

01:32:31.840 --> 01:32:33.831
You'll pay me back.

01:32:35.400 --> 01:32:38.233
- No, l...
- No, Vic and I talked about this.

01:32:39.400 --> 01:32:41.516
We don't have any kids of our own.

01:32:42.000 --> 01:32:45.595
Daisy, Jojo... you.

01:32:48.800 --> 01:32:52.110
You're my kids. So...

01:32:53.320 --> 01:32:55.834
Thanks, Leona.

01:32:55.920 --> 01:32:57.911
Hey! You're messin' up my dress.

01:33:28.160 --> 01:33:30.833
Karen, you wanna take this out?

01:33:50.200 --> 01:33:52.191
It's a great party.

01:33:56.640 --> 01:33:58.631
What do you want, Charlie?

01:34:00.400 --> 01:34:02.391
Listen.

01:34:04.000 --> 01:34:06.992
What you said about me and my father...

01:34:07.520 --> 01:34:10.080
You were right.

01:34:10.160 --> 01:34:12.913
- So?
- I owe you an apology.

01:34:14.360 --> 01:34:16.351
OK.

01:34:17.880 --> 01:34:19.871
So...

01:34:20.680 --> 01:34:23.035
So?

01:34:34.040 --> 01:34:36.838
So you like chocolate ice cream?

01:34:41.440 --> 01:34:44.159
It's my favourite.

01:34:44.240 --> 01:34:46.356
Well, this must be your lucky night.

01:35:01.360 --> 01:35:03.271
Keep it up.

01:35:16.080 --> 01:35:18.071
Thought I'd find you out here.

01:35:23.040 --> 01:35:25.190
I see you had some company in there.

01:35:29.640 --> 01:35:31.631
Who knows?

01:35:34.720 --> 01:35:37.029
God, next Thursday's Thanksgiving.

01:35:38.480 --> 01:35:40.471
Soon I'll be at college.

01:35:42.240 --> 01:35:45.152
- Do me a favour?
- What's that?

01:35:45.720 --> 01:35:48.996
Next time you take on a Yalie,
pick one your own age?

01:35:49.400 --> 01:35:51.914
- Who knows?
- Hey, you guys.

01:35:52.000 --> 01:35:56.232
You're not gonna believe what Bill's mom
just said to me. You're gonna die.

01:35:56.320 --> 01:36:01.269
She came up to me and she said "So,
when am I gonna hear some good news?"

01:36:01.360 --> 01:36:05.831
I mean, I've been married two hours
and she wants me knocked up already!

01:36:10.520 --> 01:36:12.317
I really love you guys.

01:36:23.000 --> 01:36:25.798
- You know what I wonder?
- What?

01:36:26.680 --> 01:36:30.389
What the hell do you think
Leona really puts in that pizza?

